t-adv-heading23_704120-f6 mark.kt-highlight, .wp-block-kadence-advancedheading.kt-adv-heading23_704120-f6[data-kb-block=\"kb-adv-heading23_704120-f6\"] mark.kt-highlight{font-style:normal;color:#f76a0c;-webkit-box-decoration-break:clone;box-decoration-break:clone;padding-top:0px;padding-right:0px;padding-bottom:0px;padding-left:0px;}.wp-block-kadence-advancedheading.kt-adv-heading23_704120-f6 img.kb-inline-image, .wp-block-kadence-advancedheading.kt-adv-heading23_704120-f6[data-kb-block=\"kb-adv-heading23_704120-f6\"] img.kb-inline-image{width:150px;vertical-align:baseline;}@media all and (max-width: 1024px){.wp-block-kadence-advancedheading.kt-adv-heading23_704120-f6, .wp-block-kadence-advancedheading.kt-adv-heading23_704120-f6[data-kb-block=\"kb-adv-heading23_704120-f6\"]{text-align:center!important;}}<\/style>\n<p class=\"kt-adv-heading23_704120-f6 wp-block-kadence-advancedheading\" data-kb-block=\"kb-adv-heading23_704120-f6\"><em><strong>UPDATED September 12, 2022<\/strong><\/em><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Dear Liddell&#8217;s Rentals Tenants,<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>We have come up with a Quarterly Preventative Maintenance Inspection schedule that will be somewhat easy for our tenants and ourselves to remember. All inspections will be conducted on the<strong>&nbsp;SECOND Tuesday of every third month<\/strong>. As a courtesy, we will send out a text and\/or email reminder a few days before each inspection. To ensure that you receive these reminders, please verify that we have your current contact information on file.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Please be sure that all pets\/animals are contained on inspection day. We don&#8217;t want anyone&#8217;s dog or cat darting out the door as we enter or exit.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As explained in your lease agreement, we will be checking for undetected\/unreported maintenance issues, damage, and general sanitation. Some of the issues we will be looking for include, but are not limited to:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Leaks under kitchen\/bathroom sinks or around toilets\/tubs;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Air filters are being replaced by the tenant regularly (dirty filters will be replaced by Management at Resident&#8217;s expense);<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Smoke detectors are operational (dead\/missing batteries will be replaced by Management at Resident&#8217;s expense);<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Unreported damage to the unit;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>A need for pest control service exists;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Adherence to tenant responsibilities outlined in Arkansas Code Annotated \u00a7 18-17-601, to include:<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Reasonable safety and reasonable cleanliness;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Trash is being disposed in a reasonably clean and safe manner;<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li>Plumbing fixtures (toilets, sinks, etc.) are kept reasonably clean;<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<p>As landlords, it is our legal and ethical responsibility to provide our tenants with a safe and habitable dwelling. The primary reason for this inspection is to check for maintenance issues that could become very costly if left unrepaired. We appreciate you notifying us of all issues, big or small, as even tiny problems can quickly and easily turn into large problems.<br>While we don\u2019t expect your home to look like a showroom, Arkansas statues require tenants to maintain a certain cleanliness and sanitation standard to protect not only your own health and safety, but also to protect the health and safety of your neighbors and the structural integrity of the property.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Inspections will be conducted between the hours of 8:00am and 5:00pm. Your presence during the inspection is welcome, but not required. The inspection will only take a few minutes and you can point out any maintenance concerns you may have at that time. Per your lease agreement,\u00a0&#8220;failure to allow Management or agent of Management to perform these checks will result in Resident being fined $25\u00a0per occurrence&#8221;. We appreciate your cooperation with these inspections. If you have any questions, please give us a call.<br><br>Thank you,<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"has-large-font-size\"><em><strong>Liddell&#8217;s Rentals<\/strong><\/em><\/p>\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n<\/div><\/div>\n\n\n<p><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Preventative Maintenance Inspections Inspection Schedule By Owner Inspections Occur on Different Months depending on your property owner. Please refer to the below schedule to determine on which month your residence is due for a maintenance inspection. Month of Inspection Landlord Jan, Apr, Jul, Oct Lance Liddell &amp; Eddie Rogers Feb, May, Aug, Nov Marc Liddell&#8230;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"_kadence_starter_templates_imported_post":true,"_kad_post_transparent":"","_kad_post_title":"hide","_kad_post_layout":"fullwidth","_kad_post_sidebar_id":"","_kad_post_content_style":"unboxed","_kad_post_vertical_padding":"hide","_kad_post_feature":"hide","_kad_post_feature_position":"","_kad_post_header":false,"_kad_post_footer":false,"_kad_post_classname":"","footnotes":""},"class_list":["post-23","page","type-page","status-publish","hentry"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/liddells-rentals.local\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/23","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/liddells-rentals.local\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/liddells-rentals.local\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/liddells-rentals.local\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/liddells-rentals.local\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=23"}],"version-history":[{"count":1,"href":"http:\/\/liddells-rentals.local\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/23\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":996,"href":"http:\/\/liddells-rentals.local\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/23\/revisions\/996"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"http:\/\/liddells-rentals.